{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YKUcviUM3UMGDgzrVj6FZH","type":"tool_result","content":"{\"text\":\"URL: https://demo.sourcegraph.com/github.com/sg-evals/flask--798e006f@798e006f435887adceb6aab9b57cde8e20276793/-/blob/CHANGES.rst%3FL1-80\\n1: Version 3.2.0\\n2: -------------\\n3: \\n4: Unreleased\\n5: \\n6: -   Drop support for Python 3.9. :pr:`5730`\\n7: -   Remove previously deprecated code: ``__version__``. :pr:`5648`\\n8: -   ``RequestContext`` has merged with ``AppContext``. ``RequestContext`` is now\\n9:     a deprecated alias. If an app context is already pushed, it is not reused\\n10:     when dispatching a request. This greatly simplifies the internal code for tracking\\n11:     the active context. :issue:`5639`\\n12: -   Many ``Flask`` methods involved in request dispatch now take the current\\n13:     ``AppContext`` as the first parameter, instead of using the proxy objects.\\n14:     If subclasses were overriding these methods, the old signature is detected,\\n15:     shows a deprecation warning, and will continue to work during the\\n16:     deprecation period. :issue:`5815`\\n17: -   The ``should_ignore_error`` is deprecated. Handle errors as needed in\\n18:     teardown handlers instead. :issue:`5816`\\n19: -   ``template_filter``, ``template_test``, and ``template_global`` decorators\\n20:     can be used without parentheses. :issue:`5729`\\n21: -   ``redirect`` returns a ``303`` status code by default instead of ``302``.\\n22:     This tells the client to always switch to ``GET``, rather than only\\n23:     switching ``POST`` to ``GET``. This preserves the current behavior of\\n24:     ``GET`` and ``POST`` redirects, and is also correct for frontend libraries\\n25:     such as HTMX. :issue:`5895`\\n26: \\n27: \\n28: Version 3.1.2\\n29: -------------\\n30: \\n31: Released 2025-08-19\\n32: \\n33: -   ``stream_with_context`` does not fail inside async views. :issue:`5774`\\n34: -   When using ``follow_redirects`` in the test client, the final state\\n35:     of ``session`` is correct. :issue:`5786`\\n36: -   Relax type hint for passing bytes IO to ``send_file``. :issue:`5776`\\n37: \\n38: \\n39: Version 3.1.1\\n40: -------------\\n41: \\n42: Released 2025-05-13\\n43: \\n44: -   Fix signing key selection order when key rotation is enabled via\\n45:     ``SECRET_KEY_FALLBACKS``. :ghsa:`4grg-w6v8-c28g`\\n46: -   Fix type hint for ``cli_runner.invoke``. :issue:`5645`\\n47: -   ``flask --help`` loads the app and plugins first to make sure all commands\\n48:     are shown. :issue:`5673`\\n49: -   Mark sans-io base class as being able to handle views that return\\n50:     ``AsyncIterable``. This is not accurate for Flask, but makes typing easier\\n51:     for Quart. :pr:`5659`\\n52: \\n53: \\n54: Version 3.1.0\\n55: -------------\\n56: \\n57: Released 2024-11-13\\n58: \\n59: -   Drop support for Python 3.8. :pr:`5623`\\n60: -   Update minimum dependency versions to latest feature releases.\\n61:     Werkzeug >= 3.1, ItsDangerous >= 2.2, Blinker >= 1.9. :pr:`5624,5633`\\n62: -   Provide a configuration option to control automatic option\\n63:     responses. :pr:`5496`\\n64: -   ``Flask.open_resource``/``open_instance_resource`` and\\n65:     ``Blueprint.open_resource`` take an ``encoding`` parameter to use when\\n66:     opening in text mode. It defaults to ``utf-8``. :issue:`5504`\\n67: -   ``Request.max_content_length`` can be customized per-request instead of only\\n68:     through the ``MAX_CONTENT_LENGTH`` config. Added\\n69:     ``MAX_FORM_MEMORY_SIZE`` and ``MAX_FORM_PARTS`` config. Added documentation\\n70:     about resource limits to the security page. :issue:`5625`\\n71: -   Add support for the ``Partitioned`` cookie attribute (CHIPS), with the\\n72:     ``SESSION_COOKIE_PARTITIONED`` config. :issue:`5472`\\n73: -   ``-e path`` takes precedence over default ``.env`` and ``.flaskenv`` files.\\n74:     ``load_dotenv`` loads default files in addition to a path unless\\n75:     ``load_defaults=False`` is passed. :issue:`5628`\\n76: -   Support key rotation with the ``SECRET_KEY_FALLBACKS`` config, a list of old\\n77:     secret keys that can still be used for unsigning. Extensions will need to\\n78:     add support. :issue:`5621`\\n79: -   Fix how setting ``host_matching=True`` or ``subdomain_matching=False``\\n80:     interacts with ``SERVER_NAME``. Setting ``SERVER_NAME`` no longer restricts\\n81: \"}"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e6b26004-4165-4cd1-bb6a-e52ab64b22f3","uuid":"abd7cbe8-6c66-4626-b7bd-a217e258b2cd","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:01:37.628Z","tool_use_result":{"content":"{\"text\":\"URL: https://demo.sourcegraph.com/github.com/sg-evals/flask--798e006f@798e006f435887adceb6aab9b57cde8e20276793/-/blob/CHANGES.rst%3FL1-80\\n1: Version 3.2.0\\n2: -------------\\n3: \\n4: Unreleased\\n5: \\n6: -   Drop support for Python 3.9. :pr:`5730`\\n7: -   Remove previously deprecated code: ``__version__``. :pr:`5648`\\n8: -   ``RequestContext`` has merged with ``AppContext``. ``RequestContext`` is now\\n9:     a deprecated alias. If an app context is already pushed, it is not reused\\n10:     when dispatching a request. This greatly simplifies the internal code for tracking\\n11:     the active context. :issue:`5639`\\n12: -   Many ``Flask`` methods involved in request dispatch now take the current\\n13:     ``AppContext`` as the first parameter, instead of using the proxy objects.\\n14:     If subclasses were overriding these methods, the old signature is detected,\\n15:     shows a deprecation warning, and will continue to work during the\\n16:     deprecation period. :issue:`5815`\\n17: -   The ``should_ignore_error`` is deprecated. Handle errors as needed in\\n18:     teardown handlers instead. :issue:`5816`\\n19: -   ``template_filter``, ``template_test``, and ``template_global`` decorators\\n20:     can be used without parentheses. :issue:`5729`\\n21: -   ``redirect`` returns a ``303`` status code by default instead of ``302``.\\n22:     This tells the client to always switch to ``GET``, rather than only\\n23:     switching ``POST`` to ``GET``. This preserves the current behavior of\\n24:     ``GET`` and ``POST`` redirects, and is also correct for frontend libraries\\n25:     such as HTMX. :issue:`5895`\\n26: \\n27: \\n28: Version 3.1.2\\n29: -------------\\n30: \\n31: Released 2025-08-19\\n32: \\n33: -   ``stream_with_context`` does not fail inside async views. :issue:`5774`\\n34: -   When using ``follow_redirects`` in the test client, the final state\\n35:     of ``session`` is correct. :issue:`5786`\\n36: -   Relax type hint for passing bytes IO to ``send_file``. :issue:`5776`\\n37: \\n38: \\n39: Version 3.1.1\\n40: -------------\\n41: \\n42: Released 2025-05-13\\n43: \\n44: -   Fix signing key selection order when key rotation is enabled via\\n45:     ``SECRET_KEY_FALLBACKS``. :ghsa:`4grg-w6v8-c28g`\\n46: -   Fix type hint for ``cli_runner.invoke``. :issue:`5645`\\n47: -   ``flask --help`` loads the app and plugins first to make sure all commands\\n48:     are shown. :issue:`5673`\\n49: -   Mark sans-io base class as being able to handle views that return\\n50:     ``AsyncIterable``. This is not accurate for Flask, but makes typing easier\\n51:     for Quart. :pr:`5659`\\n52: \\n53: \\n54: Version 3.1.0\\n55: -------------\\n56: \\n57: Released 2024-11-13\\n58: \\n59: -   Drop support for Python 3.8. :pr:`5623`\\n60: -   Update minimum dependency versions to latest feature releases.\\n61:     Werkzeug >= 3.1, ItsDangerous >= 2.2, Blinker >= 1.9. :pr:`5624,5633`\\n62: -   Provide a configuration option to control automatic option\\n63:     responses. :pr:`5496`\\n64: -   ``Flask.open_resource``/``open_instance_resource`` and\\n65:     ``Blueprint.open_resource`` take an ``encoding`` parameter to use when\\n66:     opening in text mode. It defaults to ``utf-8``. :issue:`5504`\\n67: -   ``Request.max_content_length`` can be customized per-request instead of only\\n68:     through the ``MAX_CONTENT_LENGTH`` config. Added\\n69:     ``MAX_FORM_MEMORY_SIZE`` and ``MAX_FORM_PARTS`` config. Added documentation\\n70:     about resource limits to the security page. :issue:`5625`\\n71: -   Add support for the ``Partitioned`` cookie attribute (CHIPS), with the\\n72:     ``SESSION_COOKIE_PARTITIONED`` config. :issue:`5472`\\n73: -   ``-e path`` takes precedence over default ``.env`` and ``.flaskenv`` files.\\n74:     ``load_dotenv`` loads default files in addition to a path unless\\n75:     ``load_defaults=False`` is passed. :issue:`5628`\\n76: -   Support key rotation with the ``SECRET_KEY_FALLBACKS`` config, a list of old\\n77:     secret keys that can still be used for unsigning. Extensions will need to\\n78:     add support. :issue:`5621`\\n79: -   Fix how setting ``host_matching=True`` or ``subdomain_matching=False``\\n80:     interacts with ``SERVER_NAME``. Setting ``SERVER_NAME`` no longer restricts\\n81: \"}","structuredContent":{"text":"URL: https://demo.sourcegraph.com/github.com/sg-evals/flask--798e006f@798e006f435887adceb6aab9b57cde8e20276793/-/blob/CHANGES.rst%3FL1-80\n1: Version 3.2.0\n2: -------------\n3: \n4: Unreleased\n5: \n6: -   Drop support for Python 3.9. :pr:`5730`\n7: -   Remove previously deprecated code: ``__version__``. :pr:`5648`\n8: -   ``RequestContext`` has merged with ``AppContext``. ``RequestContext`` is now\n9:     a deprecated alias. If an app context is already pushed, it is not reused\n10:     when dispatching a request. This greatly simplifies the internal code for tracking\n11:     the active context. :issue:`5639`\n12: -   Many ``Flask`` methods involved in request dispatch now take the current\n13:     ``AppContext`` as the first parameter, instead of using the proxy objects.\n14:     If subclasses were overriding these methods, the old signature is detected,\n15:     shows a deprecation warning, and will continue to work during the\n16:     deprecation period. :issue:`5815`\n17: -   The ``should_ignore_error`` is deprecated. Handle errors as needed in\n18:     teardown handlers instead. :issue:`5816`\n19: -   ``template_filter``, ``template_test``, and ``template_global`` decorators\n20:     can be used without parentheses. :issue:`5729`\n21: -   ``redirect`` returns a ``303`` status code by default instead of ``302``.\n22:     This tells the client to always switch to ``GET``, rather than only\n23:     switching ``POST`` to ``GET``. This preserves the current behavior of\n24:     ``GET`` and ``POST`` redirects, and is also correct for frontend libraries\n25:     such as HTMX. :issue:`5895`\n26: \n27: \n28: Version 3.1.2\n29: -------------\n30: \n31: Released 2025-08-19\n32: \n33: -   ``stream_with_context`` does not fail inside async views. :issue:`5774`\n34: -   When using ``follow_redirects`` in the test client, the final state\n35:     of ``session`` is correct. :issue:`5786`\n36: -   Relax type hint for passing bytes IO to ``send_file``. :issue:`5776`\n37: \n38: \n39: Version 3.1.1\n40: -------------\n41: \n42: Released 2025-05-13\n43: \n44: -   Fix signing key selection order when key rotation is enabled via\n45:     ``SECRET_KEY_FALLBACKS``. :ghsa:`4grg-w6v8-c28g`\n46: -   Fix type hint for ``cli_runner.invoke``. :issue:`5645`\n47: -   ``flask --help`` loads the app and plugins first to make sure all commands\n48:     are shown. :issue:`5673`\n49: -   Mark sans-io base class as being able to handle views that return\n50:     ``AsyncIterable``. This is not accurate for Flask, but makes typing easier\n51:     for Quart. :pr:`5659`\n52: \n53: \n54: Version 3.1.0\n55: -------------\n56: \n57: Released 2024-11-13\n58: \n59: -   Drop support for Python 3.8. :pr:`5623`\n60: -   Update minimum dependency versions to latest feature releases.\n61:     Werkzeug >= 3.1, ItsDangerous >= 2.2, Blinker >= 1.9. :pr:`5624,5633`\n62: -   Provide a configuration option to control automatic option\n63:     responses. :pr:`5496`\n64: -   ``Flask.open_resource``/``open_instance_resource`` and\n65:     ``Blueprint.open_resource`` take an ``encoding`` parameter to use when\n66:     opening in text mode. It defaults to ``utf-8``. :issue:`5504`\n67: -   ``Request.max_content_length`` can be customized per-request instead of only\n68:     through the ``MAX_CONTENT_LENGTH`` config. Added\n69:     ``MAX_FORM_MEMORY_SIZE`` and ``MAX_FORM_PARTS`` config. Added documentation\n70:     about resource limits to the security page. :issue:`5625`\n71: -   Add support for the ``Partitioned`` cookie attribute (CHIPS), with the\n72:     ``SESSION_COOKIE_PARTITIONED`` config. :issue:`5472`\n73: -   ``-e path`` takes precedence over default ``.env`` and ``.flaskenv`` files.\n74:     ``load_dotenv`` loads default files in addition to a path unless\n75:     ``load_defaults=False`` is passed. :issue:`5628`\n76: -   Support key rotation with the ``SECRET_KEY_FALLBACKS`` config, a list of old\n77:     secret keys that can still be used for unsigning. Extensions will need to\n78:     add support. :issue:`5621`\n79: -   Fix how setting ``host_matching=True`` or ``subdomain_matching=False``\n80:     interacts with ``SERVER_NAME``. Setting ``SERVER_NAME`` no longer restricts\n81: "}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01UvB3FqnFYa5zekrB8NTpvz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01MfiP7kKDbfJxdu5KHSxqrW","name":"mcp__sourcegraph__read_file","input":{"repo":"github.com/sg-evals/flask--3.1.0","path":"CHANGES.rst","startLine":1,"endLine":80},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2669,"cache_read_input_tokens":28601,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2669},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e6b26004-4165-4cd1-bb6a-e52ab64b22f3","uuid":"f3e0f6be-6ad0-4f26-b718-57cdd46f9529"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MfiP7kKDbfJxdu5KHSxqrW","type":"tool_result","content":"{\"text\":\"URL: https://demo.sourcegraph.com/github.com/sg-evals/flask--3.1.0@0561c2172220fd977948f718abd60928e5633516/-/blob/CHANGES.rst%3FL1-80\\n1: Version 3.1.0\\n2: -------------\\n3: \\n4: Released 2024-11-13\\n5: \\n6: -   Drop support for Python 3.8. :pr:`5623`\\n7: -   Update minimum dependency versions to latest feature releases.\\n8:     Werkzeug >= 3.1, ItsDangerous >= 2.2, Blinker >= 1.9. :pr:`5624,5633`\\n9: -   Provide a configuration option to control automatic option\\n10:     responses. :pr:`5496`\\n11: -   ``Flask.open_resource``/``open_instance_resource`` and\\n12:     ``Blueprint.open_resource`` take an ``encoding`` parameter to use when\\n13:     opening in text mode. It defaults to ``utf-8``. :issue:`5504`\\n14: -   ``Request.max_content_length`` can be customized per-request instead of only\\n15:     through the ``MAX_CONTENT_LENGTH`` config. Added\\n16:     ``MAX_FORM_MEMORY_SIZE`` and ``MAX_FORM_PARTS`` config. Added documentation\\n17:     about resource limits to the security page. :issue:`5625`\\n18: -   Add support for the ``Partitioned`` cookie attribute (CHIPS), with the\\n19:     ``SESSION_COOKIE_PARTITIONED`` config. :issue:`5472`\\n20: -   ``-e path`` takes precedence over default ``.env`` and ``.flaskenv`` files.\\n21:     ``load_dotenv`` loads default files in addition to a path unless\\n22:     ``load_defaults=False`` is passed. :issue:`5628`\\n23: -   Support key rotation with the ``SECRET_KEY_FALLBACKS`` config, a list of old\\n24:     secret keys that can still be used for unsigning. Extensions will need to\\n25:     add support. :issue:`5621`\\n26: -   Fix how setting ``host_matching=True`` or ``subdomain_matching=False``\\n27:     interacts with ``SERVER_NAME``. Setting ``SERVER_NAME`` no longer restricts\\n28:     requests to only that domain. :issue:`5553`\\n29: -   ``Request.trusted_hosts`` is checked during routing, and can be set through\\n30:     the ``TRUSTED_HOSTS`` config. :issue:`5636`\\n31: \\n32: \\n33: Version 3.0.3\\n34: -------------\\n35: \\n36: Released 2024-04-07\\n37: \\n38: -   The default ``hashlib.sha1`` may not be available in FIPS builds. Don't\\n39:     access it at import time so the developer has time to change the default.\\n40:     :issue:`5448`\\n41: -   Don't initialize the ``cli`` attribute in the sansio scaffold, but rather in\\n42:     the ``Flask`` concrete class. :pr:`5270`\\n43: \\n44: \\n45: Version 3.0.2\\n46: -------------\\n47: \\n48: Released 2024-02-03\\n49: \\n50: -   Correct type for ``jinja_loader`` property. :issue:`5388`\\n51: -   Fix error with ``--extra-files`` and ``--exclude-patterns`` CLI options.\\n52:     :issue:`5391`\\n53: \\n54: \\n55: Version 3.0.1\\n56: -------------\\n57: \\n58: Released 2024-01-18\\n59: \\n60: -   Correct type for ``path`` argument to ``send_file``. :issue:`5336`\\n61: -   Fix a typo in an error message for the ``flask run --key`` option. :pr:`5344`\\n62: -   Session data is untagged without relying on the built-in ``json.loads``\\n63:     ``object_hook``. This allows other JSON providers that don't implement that.\\n64:     :issue:`5381`\\n65: -   Address more type findings when using mypy strict mode. :pr:`5383`\\n66: \\n67: \\n68: Version 3.0.0\\n69: -------------\\n70: \\n71: Released 2023-09-30\\n72: \\n73: -   Remove previously deprecated code. :pr:`5223`\\n74: -   Deprecate the ``__version__`` attribute. Use feature detection, or\\n75:     ``importlib.metadata.version(\\\"flask\\\")``, instead. :issue:`5230`\\n76: -   Restructure the code such that the Flask (app) and Blueprint\\n77:     classes have Sans-IO bases. :pr:`5127`\\n78: -   Allow self as an argument to url_for. :pr:`5264`\\n79: -   Require Werkzeug >= 3.0.0.\\n80: \\n81: \"}"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e6b26004-4165-4cd1-bb6a-e52ab64b22f3","uuid":"6bcb05f0-a06e-4581-919f-6d7aae137b12","timestamp":"2026-03-31T21:01:38.299Z","tool_use_result":{"content":"{\"text\":\"URL: https://demo.sourcegraph.com/github.com/sg-evals/flask--3.1.0@0561c2172220fd977948f718abd60928e5633516/-/blob/CHANGES.rst%3FL1-80\\n1: Version 3.1.0\\n2: -------------\\n3: \\n4: Released 2024-11-13\\n5: \\n6: -   Drop support for Python 3.8. :pr:`5623`\\n7: -   Update minimum dependency versions to latest feature releases.\\n8:     Werkzeug >= 3.1, ItsDangerous >= 2.2, Blinker >= 1.9. :pr:`5624,5633`\\n9: -   Provide a configuration option to control automatic option\\n10:     responses. :pr:`5496`\\n11: -   ``Flask.open_resource``/``open_instance_resource`` and\\n12:     ``Blueprint.open_resource`` take an ``encoding`` parameter to use when\\n13:     opening in text mode. It defaults to ``utf-8``. :issue:`5504`\\n14: -   ``Request.max_content_length`` can be customized per-request instead of only\\n15:     through the ``MAX_CONTENT_LENGTH`` config. Added\\n16:     ``MAX_FORM_MEMORY_SIZE`` and ``MAX_FORM_PARTS`` config. Added documentation\\n17:     about resource limits to the security page. :issue:`5625`\\n18: -   Add support for the ``Partitioned`` cookie attribute (CHIPS), with the\\n19:     ``SESSION_COOKIE_PARTITIONED`` config. :issue:`5472`\\n20: -   ``-e path`` takes precedence over default ``.env`` and ``.flaskenv`` files.\\n21:     ``load_dotenv`` loads default files in addition to a path unless\\n22:     ``load_defaults=False`` is passed. :issue:`5628`\\n23: -   Support key rotation with the ``SECRET_KEY_FALLBACKS`` config, a list of old\\n24:     secret keys that can still be used for unsigning. Extensions will need to\\n25:     add support. :issue:`5621`\\n26: -   Fix how setting ``host_matching=True`` or ``subdomain_matching=False``\\n27:     interacts with ``SERVER_NAME``. Setting ``SERVER_NAME`` no longer restricts\\n28:     requests to only that domain. :issue:`5553`\\n29: -   ``Request.trusted_hosts`` is checked during routing, and can be set through\\n30:     the ``TRUSTED_HOSTS`` config. :issue:`5636`\\n31: \\n32: \\n33: Version 3.0.3\\n34: -------------\\n35: \\n36: Released 2024-04-07\\n37: \\n38: -   The default ``hashlib.sha1`` may not be available in FIPS builds. Don't\\n39:     access it at import time so the developer has time to change the default.\\n40:     :issue:`5448`\\n41: -   Don't initialize the ``cli`` attribute in the sansio scaffold, but rather in\\n42:     the ``Flask`` concrete class. :pr:`5270`\\n43: \\n44: \\n45: Version 3.0.2\\n46: -------------\\n47: \\n48: Released 2024-02-03\\n49: \\n50: -   Correct type for ``jinja_loader`` property. :issue:`5388`\\n51: -   Fix error with ``--extra-files`` and ``--exclude-patterns`` CLI options.\\n52:     :issue:`5391`\\n53: \\n54: \\n55: Version 3.0.1\\n56: -------------\\n57: \\n58: Released 2024-01-18\\n59: \\n60: -   Correct type for ``path`` argument to ``send_file``. :issue:`5336`\\n61: -   Fix a typo in an error message for the ``flask run --key`` option. :pr:`5344`\\n62: -   Session data is untagged without relying on the built-in ``json.loads``\\n63:     ``object_hook``. This allows other JSON providers that don't implement that.\\n64:     :issue:`5381`\\n65: -   Address more type findings when using mypy strict mode. :pr:`5383`\\n66: \\n67: \\n68: Version 3.0.0\\n69: -------------\\n70: \\n71: Released 2023-09-30\\n72: \\n73: -   Remove previously deprecated code. :pr:`5223`\\n74: -   Deprecate the ``__version__`` attribute. Use feature detection, or\\n75:     ``importlib.metadata.version(\\\"flask\\\")``, instead. :issue:`5230`\\n76: -   Restructure the code such that the Flask (app) and Blueprint\\n77:     classes have Sans-IO bases. :pr:`5127`\\n78: -   Allow self as an argument to url_for. :pr:`5264`\\n79: -   Require Werkzeug >= 3.0.0.\\n80: \\n81: \"}","structuredContent":{"text":"URL: https://demo.sourcegraph.com/github.com/sg-evals/flask--3.1.0@0561c2172220fd977948f718abd60928e5633516/-/blob/CHANGES.rst%3FL1-80\n1: Version 3.1.0\n2: -------------\n3: \n4: Released 2024-11-13\n5: \n6: -   Drop support for Python 3.8. :pr:`5623`\n7: -   Update minimum dependency versions to latest feature releases.\n8:     Werkzeug >= 3.1, ItsDangerous >= 2.2, Blinker >= 1.9. :pr:`5624,5633`\n9: -   Provide a configuration option to control automatic option\n10:     responses. :pr:`5496`\n11: -   ``Flask.open_resource``/``open_instance_resource`` and\n12:     ``Blueprint.open_resource`` take an ``encoding`` parameter to use when\n13:     opening in text mode. It defaults to ``utf-8``. :issue:`5504`\n14: -   ``Request.max_content_length`` can be customized per-request instead of only\n15:     through the ``MAX_CONTENT_LENGTH`` config. Added\n16:     ``MAX_FORM_MEMORY_SIZE`` and ``MAX_FORM_PARTS`` config. Added documentation\n17:     about resource limits to the security page. :issue:`5625`\n18: -   Add support for the ``Partitioned`` cookie attribute (CHIPS), with the\n19:     ``SESSION_COOKIE_PARTITIONED`` config. :issue:`5472`\n20: -   ``-e path`` takes precedence over default ``.env`` and ``.flaskenv`` files.\n21:     ``load_dotenv`` loads default files in addition to a path unless\n22:     ``load_defaults=False`` is passed. :issue:`5628`\n23: -   Support key rotation with the ``SECRET_KEY_FALLBACKS`` config, a list of old\n24:     secret keys that can still be used for unsigning. Extensions will need to\n25:     add support. :issue:`5621`\n26: -   Fix how setting ``host_matching=True`` or ``subdomain_matching=False``\n27:     interacts with ``SERVER_NAME``. Setting ``SERVER_NAME`` no longer restricts\n28:     requests to only that domain. :issue:`5553`\n29: -   ``Request.trusted_hosts`` is checked during routing, and can be set through\n30:     the ``TRUSTED_HOSTS`` config. :issue:`5636`\n31: \n32: \n33: Version 3.0.3\n34: -------------\n35: \n36: Released 2024-04-07\n37: \n38: -   The default ``hashlib.sha1`` may not be available in FIPS builds. Don't\n39:     access it at import time so the developer has time to change the default.\n40:     :issue:`5448`\n41: -   Don't initialize the ``cli`` attribute in the sansio scaffold, but rather in\n42:     the ``Flask`` concrete class. :pr:`5270`\n43: \n44: \n45: Version 3.0.2\n46: -------------\n47: \n48: Released 2024-02-03\n49: \n50: -   Correct type for ``jinja_loader`` property. :issue:`5388`\n51: -   Fix error with ``--extra-files`` and ``--exclude-patterns`` CLI options.\n52:     :issue:`5391`\n53: \n54: \n55: Version 3.0.1\n56: -------------\n57: \n58: Released 2024-01-18\n59: \n60: -   Correct type for ``path`` argument to ``send_file``. :issue:`5336`\n61: -   Fix a typo in an error message for the ``flask run --key`` option. :pr:`5344`\n62: -   Session data is untagged without relying on the built-in ``json.loads``\n63:     ``object_hook``. This allows other JSON providers that don't implement that.\n64:     :issue:`5381`\n65: -   Address more type findings when using mypy strict mode. :pr:`5383`\n66: \n67: \n68: Version 3.0.0\n69: -------------\n70: \n71: Released 2023-09-30\n72: \n73: -   Remove previously deprecated code. :pr:`5223`\n74: -   Deprecate the ``__version__`` attribute. Use feature detection, or\n75:     ``importlib.metadata.version(\"flask\")``, instead. :issue:`5230`\n76: -   Restructure the code such that the Flask (app) and Blueprint\n77:     classes have Sans-IO bases. :pr:`5127`\n78: -   Allow self as an argument to url_for. :pr:`5264`\n79: -   Require Werkzeug >= 3.0.0.\n80: \n81: "}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Dky1Vd7UJrrGEKX8ssMV2j","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So `flask--798e006f` is the unreleased 3.2.0 version (dev). Let me look for the older Flask blueprints.py to understand where the bug was. The user asked about where the nested prefix issue occurs.\n\nLooking at the current code (both 3.1.0 and 3.2.0 dev), the prefix combination logic is at lines 349-377 in `sansio/blueprints.py`. This logic APPEARS correct.\n\nBut wait, let me re-examine this case more carefully. The user describes:\n\n```python\napi_bp = Blueprint('api', __name__, url_prefix='/api')\n\n\nusers_bp = Blueprint('users', __name__, url_prefix='/users')\napi_bp.register_blueprint(users_bp)\n```\n\nWhen `app.register_blueprint(api_bp)` is called, the registration process creates a state with the api prefix, then when processing nested blueprints, it checks for url_prefix in the options first (which would be None), then falls back to the blueprint's own url_prefix of `/users`.\n\nSo the final path becomes `/api/users` as expected. This suggests the bug was fixed in an earlier version, so I should check the CHANGES.rst file to find when nested blueprint url_prefix handling was corrected.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4204,"cache_read_input_tokens":31270,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4204},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e6b26004-4165-4cd1-bb6a-e52ab64b22f3","uuid":"b0602a2e-265a-4561-8dd9-3a792d40592e"}
