{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":172737,"duration_api_ms":171560,"num_turns":19,"result":"Here's a summary of the findings:\n\n## Nested Blueprint `url_prefix` Ignored — Root Cause\n\n**File:** `src/flask/sansio/blueprints.py`\n\n### How `register_blueprint` propagates nested prefixes\n\n1. **`Blueprint.register_blueprint()`** (line 271) merely appends `(child_bp, options)` to `self._blueprints`. No URL logic runs here.\n\n2. **`Blueprint.register()`** (lines 349–377) is where prefix combination actually happens. When the parent blueprint is registered with the app, it loops over `self._blueprints` and builds a combined `url_prefix` for each child before calling `child.register(app, bp_options)`.\n\n3. **`BlueprintSetupState.__init__`** (lines 72–77) resolves `url_prefix` from options, then falls back to `blueprint.url_prefix`. This sets `state.url_prefix` used by every `add_url_rule()` call.\n\n### Where the prefix gets dropped\n\nThe bug (Flask 2.0.0, fixed in 2.0.1 via `:issue:4037`) was in `Blueprint.register()`:\n\n```python\nbp_url_prefix = bp_options.get(\"url_prefix\")  # None — not passed to register_blueprint()\n# BUG: missing fallback:\n# if bp_url_prefix is None:\n#     bp_url_prefix = blueprint.url_prefix     ← THIS LINE WAS ABSENT in 2.0.0\n```\n\nWithout the fallback, `bp_url_prefix` stays `None`, the combination condition `state.url_prefix is not None and bp_url_prefix is not None` is False, and execution falls through to `elif state.url_prefix is not None: bp_options[\"url_prefix\"] = state.url_prefix` — giving the child just `/api` instead of `/api/users`.\n\n### Trigger conditions\n1. Child blueprint created with `url_prefix=` in its constructor  \n2. `url_prefix` **not** passed as keyword arg to `parent.register_blueprint(child)`  \n3. Parent has a non-`None` url_prefix  \n4. Flask version < 2.0.1","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"e6b26004-4165-4cd1-bb6a-e52ab64b22f3","total_cost_usd":0.39493379999999995,"